WEBVTT

00:01.073 --> 00:02.740
<i>Previously on "For The People"...</i>

00:02.773 --> 00:04.897
I hired a psychiatrist
to do a full evaluation

00:04.922 --> 00:06.322
to see what we're dealing with.

00:06.356 --> 00:08.233
- Where's Sandra?
- Sandra doesn't like hospitals.

00:08.258 --> 00:09.858
- Who likes hospitals?
- It's different with Sandra.

00:09.893 --> 00:11.627
It's been my dream to have season tickets

00:11.661 --> 00:12.869
to the Yankees with you.

00:12.904 --> 00:15.007
- I want to go to games with you.
- Thank you.

00:15.032 --> 00:17.000
Opioids... we haven't brought
a single charge

00:17.035 --> 00:18.035
against a single doctor.

00:18.069 --> 00:20.070
This was <i>my</i> problem. Now it's yours.

00:20.104 --> 00:22.005
KATE: When you're focused
on hiding certain things,

00:22.040 --> 00:24.541
you get sloppy about other things.

00:24.576 --> 00:26.577
Let's find those other things.

00:26.611 --> 00:28.512
I'm glad you're back from the ATF stuff.

00:28.546 --> 00:29.947
Was that a good experience?

00:29.981 --> 00:32.516
Yes. Very good. I learned a lot.

00:32.549 --> 00:34.718
♪

00:35.787 --> 00:39.056
[ALBIN LEE MELDAU'S
"THE WEIGHT IS GONE" PLAYS]

00:39.090 --> 00:41.925
♪ Everyone knows ♪

00:41.960 --> 00:44.061
♪ The things ♪

00:44.095 --> 00:45.829
♪ You do ♪

00:48.299 --> 00:50.868
♪ All of the grief ♪

00:50.902 --> 00:52.936
♪ You put ♪

00:52.971 --> 00:54.738
♪ Me through ♪

00:56.307 --> 00:58.408
♪ Every time you ♪

00:58.443 --> 01:00.611
- ♪ Tell me how it's gonna be ♪
- [ALARM BEEPING]

01:00.645 --> 01:02.379
You set your alarm for...

01:02.413 --> 01:03.714
That's not my alarm.

01:03.748 --> 01:05.215
That's a pre-alarm, a warning.

01:05.250 --> 01:06.483
It's still dark out.

01:06.517 --> 01:08.051
I have to go to work.

01:08.086 --> 01:10.320
In three hours.

01:10.355 --> 01:11.755
I like to be early.

01:11.789 --> 01:12.923
This isn't early.

01:12.957 --> 01:15.025
This is, like, still yesterday.

01:16.327 --> 01:17.928
[ALARM BEEPING]

01:17.962 --> 01:19.897
Another warning.

01:19.931 --> 01:21.965
[SIGHS]

01:22.000 --> 01:23.901
[CHUCKLES]

01:24.247 --> 01:25.614
What?

01:25.648 --> 01:26.819
I like you.

01:26.853 --> 01:28.083
I like you, too.

01:28.117 --> 01:29.751
I "like you" like you.

01:29.786 --> 01:31.386
I like waking up next to you,

01:31.421 --> 01:33.121
despite your alarm-clock compulsion.

01:33.156 --> 01:34.990
- [CHUCKLES]
- I like your weirdness.

01:35.024 --> 01:36.592
I'm not weird.

01:36.626 --> 01:38.360
You alphabetize your soup.

01:40.650 --> 01:42.951
I like you.

01:45.522 --> 01:47.758
Too much too soon?

01:48.304 --> 01:50.973
It's still dark out. I'm aware.

01:51.007 --> 01:53.141
You only talk about feelings
when the sun is up?

02:01.851 --> 02:03.619
[ALARM BEEPING]

02:03.653 --> 02:04.987
<i>That's</i> my alarm.

02:05.622 --> 02:07.489
Okay. [GRUNTS]

02:11.628 --> 02:13.700
Now my warning.

02:14.197 --> 02:15.831
You're not going to work anytime soon.

02:15.865 --> 02:22.437
♪

02:22.472 --> 02:29.278
♪

02:29.312 --> 02:30.646
You've reached a new low.

02:30.680 --> 02:32.781
I would work on the floor in my office,

02:32.815 --> 02:34.292
but I can't see the floor in my office.

02:34.326 --> 02:36.518
There may be no floor in my office.

02:36.552 --> 02:37.686
It can't be that bad.

02:37.720 --> 02:39.521
I can't see the floor in your office.

02:39.555 --> 02:41.230
I just got a call

02:41.231 --> 02:42.798
that a former client, Carlos Payano,

02:42.832 --> 02:45.341
was detained by Customs agents at JFK

02:45.366 --> 02:46.900
on his way back from Mexico City...

02:46.935 --> 02:49.486
suspicion of drug trafficking,
body packing.

02:49.520 --> 02:51.783
They believe he ingested the drugs.

02:51.818 --> 02:53.138
Someone needs to go see him.

02:53.172 --> 02:56.326
I am being forced... forced... to attend

02:56.360 --> 02:59.136
a Second Circuit conference
on electronic discovery

02:59.137 --> 03:01.372
- today in Westchester.
- Everything you just said...

03:01.406 --> 03:02.873
I know. I know.

03:02.907 --> 03:04.108
But that puts me out for the day.

03:04.142 --> 03:05.209
You have the Slotkin hearing.

03:05.243 --> 03:06.210
Sandra...

03:06.244 --> 03:07.244
Of course.

03:07.278 --> 03:08.912
What was Payano's prior?

03:08.947 --> 03:10.180
Counterfeiting. Nothing like this.

03:10.215 --> 03:11.215
Is he still at the airport?

03:11.249 --> 03:13.250
They're taking him
to Manhattan Memorial Hospital

03:13.284 --> 03:14.785
to be X-rayed to confirm the drugs.

03:14.819 --> 03:15.853
You need to object to that.

03:15.887 --> 03:17.254
The hospital.

03:17.288 --> 03:19.256
- Is that a problem?
- No.

03:19.290 --> 03:20.624
You don't like hospitals.

03:20.658 --> 03:22.860
[SIGHS] Who likes hospitals?

03:22.894 --> 03:23.861
It's fine.

03:23.895 --> 03:25.095
I got it.

03:25.597 --> 03:27.231
Okay.

03:27.265 --> 03:31.135
♪

03:31.169 --> 03:32.803
[SIGHS]

03:32.837 --> 03:38.275
♪

