03:48.353 --> 03:50.320
- Where is she?
- Not here.

03:50.355 --> 03:52.122
- What do you mean "not here"?
- Not here.

03:52.157 --> 03:53.757
- She's in court.
- She's not in court.

03:53.792 --> 03:55.959
- A meeting.
- Nothing. I checked her calendar.

03:55.994 --> 03:57.728
You checked her calendar?

03:59.097 --> 04:00.794
- How carefully?
- Maybe she's sick?

04:00.828 --> 04:02.166
Her immune system's a fortress.

04:02.200 --> 04:03.282
Nothing gets in.

04:03.316 --> 04:04.435
Well, that means either she's late

04:04.469 --> 04:06.303
or she's moved to a different floor.

04:06.337 --> 04:08.806
But she's maintaining
this office to throw us off.

04:08.840 --> 04:10.474
She'll probably come by
from time to time,

04:10.508 --> 04:11.750
maybe hire a body double.

04:11.784 --> 04:12.829
On the new floor,

04:12.864 --> 04:14.645
she's probably working
under an assumed name,

04:14.679 --> 04:15.782
possibly a whole new identity.

04:15.817 --> 04:17.214
We'll need to work together on this.

04:18.216 --> 04:19.370
I'll take 18 to 20.

04:19.404 --> 04:21.250
You start on 22 and work your way up.

04:21.286 --> 04:22.319
- Hey.
- Hey.

04:22.353 --> 04:24.188
Hey. Where were you?

04:24.222 --> 04:25.689
That's none of your business.

04:25.723 --> 04:27.191
- You're late.
- I'm not late.

04:27.225 --> 04:28.459
The sun is out.

04:28.493 --> 04:29.660
What were you doing?

04:29.694 --> 04:32.362
Enjoying my morning.

04:32.397 --> 04:33.831
Which, thanks to you two,
I'm not doing anymore.

04:33.865 --> 04:34.932
Why are you both here?

04:34.966 --> 04:36.100
I gave you both offices.

04:36.134 --> 04:37.167
Thank you. God... Thank you.

04:37.202 --> 04:39.136
No, stay. I'm glad you're here.

04:39.170 --> 04:40.838
What? No.

04:40.872 --> 04:42.206
Max Gillespie is stepping down.

04:42.240 --> 04:43.807
Taking a job in Main Justice.

04:43.842 --> 04:45.042
- LEONARD: Wow.
- KATE: That's huge.

04:45.076 --> 04:46.376
Okay. Yes. Wow.

04:46.411 --> 04:47.544
Who is Max Gillespie?

04:47.579 --> 04:49.613
Chief of the Public Corruption Unit.

04:49.647 --> 04:50.814
Any thoughts about...

04:50.849 --> 04:52.182
You're not replacing him.

04:52.217 --> 04:53.350
I wasn't suggesting...

04:53.384 --> 04:54.618
- You were.
- You were.

04:54.652 --> 04:55.819
ROGER: I'm reassigning
Gillespie's case load,

04:55.854 --> 04:57.072
and I'm putting you three

04:57.106 --> 04:58.689
on an investigation into Bill Shales.

04:58.723 --> 05:00.989
Bill Shales, the Governor of New York.

05:01.024 --> 05:02.306
For now.

05:02.341 --> 05:03.788
A few days ago, we got a tip that,

05:03.822 --> 05:04.928
after Senator Reyes died,

05:04.963 --> 05:06.037
instead of appointing her replacement,

05:06.071 --> 05:08.198
Shales had been trying
to sell her Senate seat.

05:08.233 --> 05:10.200
The Governor is trying to sell
a Senate seat?

05:10.235 --> 05:11.802
This was not covered
on Schoolhouse Rock, I know.

05:11.836 --> 05:14.138
- It's upsetting.
- Yes.

05:14.172 --> 05:15.506
And deeply illegal.

05:15.540 --> 05:17.007
Shales has been extorting

05:17.041 --> 05:18.842
campaign donations for himself,

05:18.877 --> 05:20.410
positions on corporate boards
for his wife,

05:20.445 --> 05:21.641
whatever he can get.

05:21.675 --> 05:23.514
He has staffers putting out
feelers for the best offer.

05:23.548 --> 05:24.848
It wouldn't have been such a bad plan

05:24.883 --> 05:25.883
if Shales hadn't created

05:25.917 --> 05:27.818
such a toxic work environment
in the statehouse,

05:27.852 --> 05:29.753
but now Shales' aides
are turning on each other.

05:29.787 --> 05:31.722
We have cases against three of them.

05:31.756 --> 05:33.590
To make a case
against Shales himself, though,

05:33.625 --> 05:35.359
we need someone
to directly implicate him,

05:35.393 --> 05:36.293
and we don't have that yet.

05:36.327 --> 05:38.428
And the trick is,
we have to get to Shales

05:38.463 --> 05:40.030
before he realizes that we're on to him

05:40.064 --> 05:41.265
and starts destroying evidence.

05:41.299 --> 05:42.199
There's a wiretap in place.

05:42.233 --> 05:44.401
I need you digging up
whatever you can find

05:44.435 --> 05:45.836
so that when we catch him in the act,

05:45.870 --> 05:47.404
we're ready to go.

05:47.438 --> 05:48.672
Case files are
in the secure conference room

05:48.706 --> 05:50.774
- on the 22nd floor.
- KATE: Oh, sorry.

05:50.808 --> 05:51.975
Maybe I missed it

05:52.009 --> 05:53.610
while I was praying for you all to leave.

05:53.645 --> 05:54.912
Whose case is this?

05:54.946 --> 05:56.180
Yours.

05:56.214 --> 05:57.347
KATE: Uh...
- When you do that thing

05:57.382 --> 05:58.348
- with your head...
- Sorry, um?

05:58.383 --> 05:59.383
Yours, all of yours.

05:59.417 --> 06:00.617
This is a major prosecution.

06:00.652 --> 06:02.419
A little teamwork won't kill you.

06:02.453 --> 06:04.092
Or it might. Time will tell.

06:04.127 --> 06:06.390
I'll be out of the office for the
rest of the day. You're on your own.

06:06.424 --> 06:07.724
And if you screw this up, I'll be angry,

06:07.759 --> 06:08.959
and you don't want to see me angry.

06:09.519 --> 06:11.094
SETH: I feel like I have seen that.

06:11.129 --> 06:12.731
You haven't.

06:13.464 --> 06:16.967
[KEYS CLACKING]

06:17.001 --> 06:18.402
I see you!

06:18.436 --> 06:19.736
We can get you out of there!

06:19.771 --> 06:20.871
Stay calm!

06:20.905 --> 06:22.039
I'll be back...

06:22.073 --> 06:24.274
[IMITATING ECHOING] ...back, back.

06:24.309 --> 06:28.247
Because there's so much... stuff.

06:28.282 --> 06:30.981
- You okay?
- Yeah. New case. I'm fine.

06:31.015 --> 06:32.549
Can I help? I'm happy to swap.

06:33.651 --> 06:35.452
- Really?
- Really.

06:35.486 --> 06:37.921
Except... I don't actually
have anything to swap.

06:37.956 --> 06:39.256
I'm pretty light right now.

06:39.290 --> 06:40.290
[SIGHS] I'm fine.

06:40.325 --> 06:41.291
You sure?

06:41.326 --> 06:42.626
You'd be doing me a favor.

06:42.660 --> 06:44.628
I'm okay, really.

06:44.662 --> 06:51.802
♪

06:51.836 --> 06:53.270
[SIGHS]

06:53.304 --> 06:56.340
<i>Appointing our next senator
is a great honor</i>

06:56.374 --> 06:58.475
<i>and an even greater responsibility.</i>

06:58.509 --> 07:00.777
<i>I have launched a comprehensive search</i>

07:00.812 --> 07:02.446
<i>for the right candidate.</i>

07:02.480 --> 07:04.615
<i>Someone with integrity,</i>

07:04.649 --> 07:06.350
<i>who is forward-thinking yet has...</i>

07:06.384 --> 07:08.085
- [TV TURNS OFF]
- A lot of liquid cash and connections.

07:08.119 --> 07:09.319
This guy's good.

07:09.354 --> 07:10.254
We should set him up,

07:10.288 --> 07:12.298
send in some rich Republican with a wire.

07:12.332 --> 07:14.171
A sting? That's your go-to now?

07:14.205 --> 07:15.792
It makes sense. It's fast, effective...

07:15.827 --> 07:17.728
It's a waste of resources. The
phones are already tapped.

07:17.762 --> 07:19.791
No way Shales is talking
about this stuff on the phone.

07:19.825 --> 07:21.131
- He's too savvy.
- Leonard's right.

07:21.165 --> 07:23.267
The wiretap only pays off
when he slips up,

07:23.301 --> 07:24.394
and that's gonna take time,

07:24.428 --> 07:26.103
which is why we should run a sting.

07:26.137 --> 07:27.771
We need to play this man-to-man.

07:27.805 --> 07:29.172
I'll focus on Shales.

07:29.207 --> 07:30.495
Politicians are shaping up
to be a specialty of mine.

07:30.530 --> 07:32.342
Mm-hmm, though you've yet
to prosecute one?

07:32.376 --> 07:34.211
You've got Tim Klein,
the Governor's chief of staff,

07:34.245 --> 07:35.349
tennis partner, and best friend.

07:35.383 --> 07:37.347
And, Seth, you're on the aides.

07:37.382 --> 07:38.615
I'm just trying to see your badge

07:38.650 --> 07:40.450
where it says you're
the work coordinator.

07:40.485 --> 07:41.618
Someone's got to take the short straw.

07:41.653 --> 07:42.686
It should be you.

07:42.720 --> 07:44.054
No one's getting the short straw.

07:44.088 --> 07:45.722
You heard Roger. We're
getting credit as a unit,

07:45.757 --> 07:47.259
even though I'll be doing all the work.

07:47.294 --> 07:48.358
Let's divide and conquer.

07:48.393 --> 07:49.993
Kate, you go through these.
Leonard, you can take these.

07:50.028 --> 07:51.495
- I've got the rest.
- You're the boss now?

07:52.140 --> 07:53.363
Or you take them. I don't care.

07:53.398 --> 07:54.865
But we need to start working.

07:54.899 --> 07:56.233
Well, not without a plan.

07:56.267 --> 07:58.035
- This is the plan.
- [CELLPHONE RINGS]

07:59.570 --> 08:00.964
Hey.

08:01.506 --> 08:04.975
I guess the work coordinator
just sets his own breaks.

08:05.009 --> 08:06.344
[DOOR CLOSES]

08:09.947 --> 08:18.088
♪

08:18.122 --> 08:26.330
♪

08:26.364 --> 08:34.538
♪

08:37.741 --> 08:39.342
Remember when Roger said the trick is

08:39.376 --> 08:40.919
that Shales can't find out
we're investigating him?

08:40.953 --> 08:42.212
Yeah, uh-huh.

08:42.246 --> 08:43.179
We remember, because that
was like 10 minutes ago.

08:43.214 --> 08:45.349
That was a call
from a friend of a friend...

08:45.383 --> 08:46.747
fact checker at the <i>Sentinel.</i>

08:46.781 --> 08:48.619
They know we're looking into
Shales about the Senate seat,

08:48.654 --> 08:49.853
and they're gonna run a story on it,

08:49.887 --> 08:52.255
which means the Governor,
all his top aides,

08:52.290 --> 08:53.790
will know we're on to them.

08:53.825 --> 08:54.725
They're gonna cover their tracks,

08:54.759 --> 08:56.393
destroy evidence, intimidate witnesses.

08:56.427 --> 08:57.427
If that happens...

08:57.462 --> 08:58.428
KATE: If that happens,
this case will be over,

08:58.463 --> 09:00.897
and we'll have lost
an enormous opportunity

09:00.932 --> 09:02.232
to attack serious political corruption.

09:02.266 --> 09:05.001
And Roger will be angry.

09:06.404 --> 09:08.605
I'm just saying. Let's
not lose sight of that.

09:11.175 --> 09:17.940
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

09:18.163 --> 09:22.567
♪

09:24.104 --> 09:25.171
Hey.

09:25.205 --> 09:26.483
Hey.

09:27.007 --> 09:28.274
You're going the wrong way.

09:28.308 --> 09:29.675
This is definitely the right way.

09:29.710 --> 09:31.010
Back that way are signs with the words

09:31.044 --> 09:32.345
"electronic discovery" on them.

09:32.379 --> 09:33.746
You're leaving?

09:33.780 --> 09:35.081
I'm already gone.

09:35.115 --> 09:36.582
Attendance is required.

09:36.617 --> 09:38.017
Signing the form is required.

09:38.051 --> 09:39.619
I signed the form. Now I'm leaving.

09:39.653 --> 09:41.020
- Where are you going?
- To have fun.

09:41.054 --> 09:42.188
We're in Westchester.

09:42.222 --> 09:43.631
You can find fun anywhere.

09:43.665 --> 09:46.159
- You don't seem like yourself.
- I'm not myself.

09:46.193 --> 09:48.127
This is the one day a year
I am not myself...

09:48.162 --> 09:49.695
one day when I answer to no one

09:49.730 --> 09:51.130
and do exactly what I want to do.

09:51.165 --> 09:53.366
You're a prosecutor.
You do that every day.

09:53.400 --> 09:54.800
I see your point. I do.

09:54.835 --> 09:56.079
This is different, though.

09:57.304 --> 09:58.504
Every year at this conference,

09:58.539 --> 10:00.006
I shuffle through that dreadful line,

10:00.040 --> 10:02.108
I sign, and then I leave.

10:02.142 --> 10:03.209
For the day.

10:03.243 --> 10:05.511
Happy, on an adventure.

10:05.546 --> 10:07.620
Roger Gunn's Grand Day Out.

10:07.654 --> 10:09.649
Grand, because
it's the Westchester Grand.

10:09.683 --> 10:10.983
Yeah, I got it.

10:11.018 --> 10:12.285
You're welcome to come along.

10:12.319 --> 10:13.686
I can't.

10:14.521 --> 10:15.521
Okay.

10:15.556 --> 10:17.123
Have fun in there learning
about harvesting data.

10:17.157 --> 10:18.057
It's great.

10:18.091 --> 10:20.226
I think you'll really enjoy the deep dive

10:20.260 --> 10:22.295
into technology-assisted document review.

10:23.504 --> 10:25.097
[SIGHS]

10:33.507 --> 10:35.241
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

10:35.275 --> 10:38.144
♪

10:38.178 --> 10:41.180
[MONITORS BEEPING]

10:41.215 --> 10:43.082
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

10:43.116 --> 10:44.584
♪

10:44.618 --> 10:46.052
WOMAN: Do you need to sit down?

10:46.086 --> 10:47.119
Miss?

10:47.154 --> 10:48.988
If you check in with triage,
they'll register you.

10:49.022 --> 10:50.323
I-I'm an attorney.

10:50.357 --> 10:51.324
My client's in custody here.

10:51.358 --> 10:53.559
Second floor,
past the interior elevator bank.

10:53.594 --> 10:59.065
♪

10:59.099 --> 11:00.888
- Anything?
- SETH: Yeah.

11:01.768 --> 11:04.737
These aides really hate each other.

11:04.771 --> 11:06.572
I'm six pages deep into an e-mail fight

11:06.607 --> 11:07.740
between Natalie and Simon

11:07.774 --> 11:09.575
that started when Natalie accused Simon

11:09.610 --> 11:11.611
of taking credit for a speech
that Natalie wrote.

11:11.645 --> 11:14.247
Then, Natalie left a can of empty tuna

11:14.281 --> 11:16.215
in the trash can outside Simon's office.

11:16.250 --> 11:18.150
Simon doesn't like tuna.

11:19.119 --> 11:20.119
Anything on Shales?

11:20.153 --> 11:21.786
Oh, no. Not yet.

11:21.820 --> 11:23.256
We don't have a case against Shales

11:23.290 --> 11:24.490
with what's in this room.

11:24.524 --> 11:26.762
Oh, I was wondering which one
of you was gonna go lazy first.

11:26.796 --> 11:28.961
I was betting on Seth, but either way...

11:28.996 --> 11:30.296
Why don't we use what we do have

11:30.330 --> 11:31.501
and bring charges against the aides?

11:31.535 --> 11:33.320
We're going after the Governor,
not the aides.

11:33.354 --> 11:35.301
Exactly what you said in our opioid case.

11:35.335 --> 11:36.569
We were supposed to get the doctor

11:36.603 --> 11:37.536
for prescription-drug fraud,

11:37.571 --> 11:39.205
but then we got him
for human trafficking.

11:39.239 --> 11:40.773
Maybe we bring charges against the aides

11:40.807 --> 11:41.774
and see what happens.

11:41.808 --> 11:43.376
Sometimes you have to think
outside the box.

11:43.410 --> 11:44.410
Aren't you thinking inside the box?

11:44.444 --> 11:45.478
Like that <i>actual</i> box?

11:45.512 --> 11:48.648
Look, you guys are focusing on
the wrong thing here.

11:48.682 --> 11:50.483
We need to stop the story
from coming out.

11:50.517 --> 11:51.984
That is what is important now.

11:52.019 --> 11:54.287
So, why don't I call the reporter,

11:54.321 --> 11:56.658
bring her in, use a little charm?

11:57.624 --> 11:58.791
Or a lot.

11:58.825 --> 12:00.159
I can offer to give them the tip

12:00.193 --> 12:01.271
right before we go in for the arrest.

12:01.306 --> 12:03.396
We get the bigger fish,
they get the bigger story.

12:04.165 --> 12:05.935
- I think that's good.
- Thank you.

12:05.969 --> 12:08.334
- But he should do it.
- What?

12:08.368 --> 12:10.169
Did you hear the part about the charm?

12:10.203 --> 12:11.270
Yeah, I did,

12:11.305 --> 12:13.572
and I think Seth can pull it off.

12:13.607 --> 12:16.575
He's real, Midwestern,
relatable, attractive...

12:16.610 --> 12:17.643
- SETH: Thank you.
- In a bland,

12:17.678 --> 12:19.789
- non-threatening sort of way.
- Sorry?

12:19.824 --> 12:22.315
If any of us can convince
this reporter to stand down,

12:22.349 --> 12:23.905
- it's him.
- Me.

12:23.939 --> 12:25.039
You're talking about me?

12:25.073 --> 12:26.385
I'm right here.

12:26.420 --> 12:29.989
If we had another option, I'd take it.

12:32.292 --> 12:34.794
Hey. It's Leonard Knox.

12:34.828 --> 12:36.996
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY OVER P.A.]

12:37.030 --> 12:39.265
- SANDRA: Mr. Payano?
- Yes.

12:39.299 --> 12:40.866
- I'm your attorney, Sandra Bell.
- STAUB: Do not touch him.

12:40.901 --> 12:41.867
SANDRA: This man is my client.

12:41.902 --> 12:42.768
Who is in charge?

12:42.803 --> 12:44.437
STAUB: Not me and definitely not you.

12:44.471 --> 12:46.939
- Who is in charge?
- FBI. Agent Goode.

12:46.973 --> 12:48.607
You can speak to him when they
get back with the X-ray results.

12:48.642 --> 12:50.276
You were already X-rayed?

12:50.310 --> 12:51.944
I said no. They didn't listen.

12:53.680 --> 12:55.848
Those results are inadmissible.

12:55.882 --> 12:58.351
Maybe take your teeth
out of my ankle for a sec

12:58.385 --> 12:59.618
and tell me who you are.

12:59.653 --> 13:01.887
Sandra Bell. I'm Mr. Payano's attorney.

13:01.922 --> 13:02.722
Your client is likely

13:02.756 --> 13:04.357
full of cocaine packages, Ms. Bell.

13:04.391 --> 13:05.816
Did the X-ray show that?

13:05.850 --> 13:07.460
The X-ray was inconclusive.

13:07.494 --> 13:09.528
- Then he's free to go.
- I said "inconclusive."

13:09.563 --> 13:10.863
The only way to know for sure

13:10.897 --> 13:12.398
is to do a CT scan on Mr. Payano.

13:12.432 --> 13:13.881
Which you are not going to do.

13:13.916 --> 13:15.468
If he's not hiding anything...

13:15.502 --> 13:17.169
Don't try that. Don't.

13:17.204 --> 13:18.404
You're an agent with the FBI,

13:18.438 --> 13:20.139
not some traffic cop in Sarasota.

13:20.173 --> 13:21.307
You know what the Fourth Amendment is,

13:21.341 --> 13:22.541
and whether you had probable cause

13:22.576 --> 13:24.076
to detain Mr. Payano
in the first place...

13:24.111 --> 13:25.344
and I doubt that you did...

13:25.379 --> 13:26.916
there is absolutely no basis

13:26.950 --> 13:28.247
on which to continue to hold him

13:28.281 --> 13:29.648
if the X-rays are inconclusive,

13:29.683 --> 13:31.544
which means we are leaving.

13:32.619 --> 13:35.187
You defended, uh, Kirk Keener,
didn't you?

13:36.007 --> 13:37.189
What?

13:37.224 --> 13:38.657
DEA Agent Kirk Keener.

13:38.692 --> 13:40.760
Charged with leaving that guy
in the holding cell.

13:40.794 --> 13:43.362
- That was you, right?
- Yes.

13:44.015 --> 13:47.833
I appreciate what you all did for him.

13:47.868 --> 13:50.063
Let me see what I can do here.

13:53.807 --> 13:55.674
[SIGHS]

13:55.709 --> 14:00.546
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

14:00.580 --> 14:02.248
Are you going to want
to attend the breakout session

14:02.282 --> 14:04.771
on crafting effective search terms?

14:04.805 --> 14:08.888
♪

14:08.922 --> 14:10.723
ROGER: You ready?

14:10.757 --> 14:12.558
♪

14:12.592 --> 14:14.560
I was gonna give you five more minutes.

14:14.594 --> 14:16.395
♪

14:16.430 --> 14:17.596
Shall we?

14:17.631 --> 14:19.087
♪

14:19.121 --> 14:20.266
We shall.

14:20.300 --> 14:26.939
♪

14:26.973 --> 14:33.312
♪

14:33.346 --> 14:35.214
Oh. She's nodding, she's nodding.

14:35.248 --> 14:36.425
This is good.

14:36.459 --> 14:38.117
He probably asked her
if his hair looks stupid.

14:38.151 --> 14:40.920
He's talking, um...

14:40.954 --> 14:42.621
asking her something.

14:42.656 --> 14:45.324
She has a weird thing
happening with her jaw.

14:45.358 --> 14:46.892
You're done. It's my turn.

14:50.363 --> 14:51.831
He's gesturing too much.

14:51.865 --> 14:53.232
Looks like he's doing a magic trick.

14:53.266 --> 14:54.366
Where were you this morning?

14:55.035 --> 14:56.302
- Nowhere.
- That's impossible.

14:56.336 --> 14:57.670
- You must've been somewhere.
- I was home.

14:57.704 --> 14:59.438
- Doing what?
- Doesn't matter.

14:59.473 --> 15:02.107
- You're never late.
- And I wasn't late today.

15:02.142 --> 15:04.109
- You were later than usual.
- What's going on in there?

15:04.144 --> 15:05.377
This should not be a difficult question.

15:05.411 --> 15:07.813
Calm down. You're being ridiculous.

15:09.115 --> 15:10.449
It's over. They're coming out.

15:14.855 --> 15:15.821
How'd it go?

15:15.856 --> 15:17.456
I like her.

15:17.491 --> 15:18.520
She grew up in the same town
my mom did...

15:18.554 --> 15:20.092
<i>What</i> happened?

15:20.126 --> 15:21.208
Right. Okay.

15:21.242 --> 15:22.995
Well, they're not gonna stop the story.

15:23.029 --> 15:24.129
That's the bad news.

15:24.164 --> 15:27.199
The worse news is, it's going
online at 9:00 tonight.

15:27.234 --> 15:29.835
They are not backing down at all.

15:29.870 --> 15:31.170
♪

15:31.204 --> 15:33.639
Unless someone more powerful than us

15:33.673 --> 15:35.040
makes them back down.

15:35.075 --> 15:40.312
♪

15:40.347 --> 15:41.780
Unh-unh, no.

15:41.815 --> 15:43.315
Not you two, not again.

15:43.350 --> 15:47.152
♪

15:49.593 --> 15:51.160
Have you two forgotten what happened

15:51.194 --> 15:52.661
when you came to my home at midnight

15:52.696 --> 15:54.530
requesting 25 baseless search warrants?

15:54.564 --> 15:57.436
No, and I agree that Mr. Oliver

15:57.461 --> 15:59.596
had a terrible half-baked plan
that evening,

15:59.630 --> 16:00.830
but if you recall,

16:00.865 --> 16:02.765
that case ended with a big victory...

16:02.800 --> 16:03.867
You.

16:04.864 --> 16:06.282
Talk.

16:07.605 --> 16:08.738
LEONARD: Your Honor,
we have reason to believe

16:08.772 --> 16:11.274
that Governor Shales is
selling our vacant Senate seat

16:11.308 --> 16:12.469
to the highest bidder.

16:12.847 --> 16:15.211
And we're not the only ones
looking into him.

16:15.246 --> 16:17.280
The <i>New York Sentinel</i> is
set to publish a story tonight

16:17.314 --> 16:19.082
that will blow
our investigation wide open.

16:19.116 --> 16:20.450
Once it comes out,

16:20.484 --> 16:21.551
all the parties involved

16:21.585 --> 16:22.919
have the chance to bury evidence,

16:22.953 --> 16:24.787
and Shales gets away
with breaking the law,

16:24.822 --> 16:26.789
which is why we need you
to grant an injunction,

16:26.824 --> 16:29.125
preventing the paper
from publishing this story.

16:29.160 --> 16:30.860
We understand that prior restraint

16:30.895 --> 16:32.295
is an extraordinary measure,

16:32.329 --> 16:35.031
but these are extraordinary
circumstances.

16:35.065 --> 16:37.600
Under Nebraska Press Association
v. Stuart,

16:37.635 --> 16:40.203
there is an exception to the
presumption of unconstitutionality

16:40.237 --> 16:41.971
when there is a clear and present danger

16:42.006 --> 16:42.939
that pre-trial press...

16:42.973 --> 16:45.408
I'm familiar with
Nebraska Press, Mr. Knox.

16:47.448 --> 16:49.913
And extraordinary circumstances.

16:52.356 --> 16:56.359
In 1971, I was a first-year AUSA,

16:56.541 --> 16:58.708
right here in the Southern District,

16:58.733 --> 17:00.434
just like you.

17:00.459 --> 17:01.424
<i>The New York Times</i>

17:01.458 --> 17:03.493
began publishing a series of articles

17:03.527 --> 17:05.383
based on the Pentagon Papers.

17:05.964 --> 17:07.730
We believed publishing those articles

17:07.765 --> 17:09.799
jeopardized national security.

17:09.833 --> 17:14.304
So we went before a judge, just like me,

17:14.338 --> 17:15.771
and asked him for an injunction.

17:15.806 --> 17:18.775
I thought our argument
was strong, persuasive,

17:18.809 --> 17:20.643
just like yours.

17:20.678 --> 17:22.612
But two weeks later,

17:22.646 --> 17:25.515
the Supreme Court sided with the <i>Times.</i>

17:26.319 --> 17:29.419
The government must meet
a very heavy burden

17:29.453 --> 17:31.284
to justify prior restraint.

17:32.022 --> 17:34.824
You make a compelling argument, Mr. Knox,

17:34.858 --> 17:36.831
but you fail to meet that burden.

17:37.895 --> 17:39.329
The answer's no.

17:43.734 --> 17:49.439
♪

17:49.473 --> 17:55.144
♪

17:55.179 --> 17:56.779
JILL: This is the day

17:56.814 --> 17:58.715
you get to do whatever you want,

17:58.749 --> 18:00.850
- and this is what you want?
- ROGER: Yes.

18:00.884 --> 18:02.852
- It's dark...
- Yes.

18:02.886 --> 18:04.661
It's not that clean, either.

18:04.695 --> 18:06.155
Old.

18:06.190 --> 18:08.224
Why do you like coming here again?

18:08.259 --> 18:11.027
Years ago, I had a case...
one of my first cases...

18:11.061 --> 18:12.528
Mafia case, Coravano family.

18:13.546 --> 18:15.965
One of the captains, Jimmy Sant'Ambrogio

18:16.000 --> 18:17.137
agreed to cooperate,

18:17.171 --> 18:19.168
so Byrne sent me up here to talk to him.

18:19.203 --> 18:21.604
Met with him right here, maybe 10 times.

18:23.540 --> 18:25.742
Didn't Jimmy Sant'Ambrogio

18:25.776 --> 18:28.011
- die of a heart attack in a restaurant?
- Yeah.

18:28.045 --> 18:29.679
Right there, where you're sitting.

18:29.713 --> 18:31.714
He was 37.

18:31.749 --> 18:33.716
I watched him die.

18:37.554 --> 18:39.355
[LAUGHING]

18:42.092 --> 18:43.059
It was really weird.

18:43.093 --> 18:45.147
It messed up our case, too.

18:45.194 --> 18:48.197
Years later, when I moved out of
the city with Renee and the kids,

18:48.232 --> 18:49.232
I'd sneak back here,

18:49.266 --> 18:51.768
and Jimmy's brother, Sal,
who owned the place,

18:51.802 --> 18:54.158
he was really good to me.

18:54.805 --> 18:56.039
When we went through the divorce,

18:56.073 --> 18:57.040
I would hide in here,

18:57.074 --> 19:00.009
and Renee's lawyer was
too scared to come in.

19:00.044 --> 19:01.744
Breadstick?

19:01.779 --> 19:03.579
I don't see you hiding from a lawyer.

19:03.614 --> 19:04.914
I wasn't hiding from the lawyer.

19:04.948 --> 19:06.416
I was hiding from the divorce.

19:06.450 --> 19:08.851
It's my big failure.

19:08.886 --> 19:10.853
You know, until you beat me
in the DEA case.

19:10.888 --> 19:13.589
[SIGHS]

19:13.624 --> 19:15.425
When I was in here, I would just...

19:15.459 --> 19:17.515
kind of forget about it.

19:18.429 --> 19:20.763
Just think about watching Jimmy die.

19:20.798 --> 19:26.869
♪

19:26.904 --> 19:28.204
Okay, that was great.

19:28.238 --> 19:29.572
Let's go. We're gonna be late.

19:29.606 --> 19:31.774
Kind of wondering
if I made the right choice,

19:31.809 --> 19:33.209
skipping the e-discovery.

19:37.643 --> 19:39.282
KATE: It feels like
we should do something,

19:39.316 --> 19:41.884
like... have a last meal
or... see the ocean.

19:41.919 --> 19:43.820
This doesn't have to be a total loss.

19:43.854 --> 19:46.255
- We can still charge the aides.
- Stop.

19:46.290 --> 19:48.057
You sound like losers.

19:48.092 --> 19:50.226
We are not losers. We are AUSAs.

19:50.260 --> 19:51.661
We're at the top of the food chain.

19:51.695 --> 19:52.995
So we didn't get the injunction.

19:53.030 --> 19:54.464
That gives us eight hours
to build a case.

19:54.498 --> 19:56.299
- And how are we gonna do that?
- Not by giving up.

19:56.333 --> 19:58.308
I never said we should give up. I
said we should charge the aides.

19:58.343 --> 20:00.169
- Same difference.
- Not remotely.

20:00.204 --> 20:01.571
Want to know what your problem is?

20:01.605 --> 20:02.772
- I don't have a problem.
- Guys.

20:02.806 --> 20:05.074
- Yeah, you do. You think you're...
- Guys, stop fighting!

20:05.109 --> 20:07.393
- The aides... that's the answer.
- Thank you.

20:07.427 --> 20:09.512
No. Not charging them...
approaching them.

20:09.546 --> 20:11.914
We know they're fighting.
They hate their jobs.

20:11.949 --> 20:13.015
Let's use it,

20:13.050 --> 20:14.317
get them to implicate the Governor.

20:14.351 --> 20:15.485
What if they tell the Governor?

20:15.519 --> 20:16.753
[SIGHS] He's gonna find out

20:16.787 --> 20:17.794
when the story breaks anyway.

20:17.829 --> 20:19.155
- She's got a point.
- Don't talk.

20:19.588 --> 20:20.622
Let's go.

20:22.960 --> 20:27.029
SANDRA: 10, 1, 2, 3, 4,

20:27.064 --> 20:29.832
5, 6, 7...

20:29.867 --> 20:31.434
Are you okay?

20:31.468 --> 20:32.835
Yeah. I'm fine.

20:32.870 --> 20:34.036
Really?

20:34.071 --> 20:35.723
Yes.

20:35.758 --> 20:37.840
You look like they told me
I looked at the airport...

20:37.875 --> 20:39.308
nervous, sweating.

20:40.735 --> 20:41.878
Were you?

20:41.912 --> 20:43.146
Yeah.

20:43.180 --> 20:45.281
I don't know. Probably.

20:45.315 --> 20:47.016
I've got a prior and a beard,

20:47.050 --> 20:48.985
and my name's Carlos Payano,

20:49.019 --> 20:50.720
on his way back from Mexico.

20:50.754 --> 20:52.321
I'm used to getting stopped,

20:52.356 --> 20:54.023
and it still makes me nervous.

20:54.057 --> 20:55.758
I'm gonna get you out of here.

20:56.827 --> 20:58.461
They can run the test.

20:58.495 --> 21:01.030
- It's okay.
- It's not okay.

21:01.064 --> 21:02.565
I don't know what you have in you.

21:02.599 --> 21:04.400
That's not the point. The point
is, you cannot be subjected

21:04.435 --> 21:07.003
to a warrantless search
with no probably cause.

21:09.373 --> 21:10.506
So?

21:10.541 --> 21:11.374
Sorry for the wait.

21:11.408 --> 21:13.643
Orders are to take Payano for the CT.

21:13.677 --> 21:15.011
- No!
- The inconclusive X-ray,

21:15.045 --> 21:16.913
together with Mr. Payano's behavior,

21:16.947 --> 21:19.015
- constitutes probable cause.
- No.

21:19.049 --> 21:20.098
Listen.

21:20.132 --> 21:21.758
You can argue to suppress later.

21:21.792 --> 21:23.986
Right now, we're taking him.

21:24.021 --> 21:29.392
♪

21:29.426 --> 21:30.526
- [PHONE RINGING]
- Um...

21:30.561 --> 21:32.328
ALLISON: <i>You've reached
the voice-mail of Al...</i>

21:32.362 --> 21:33.362
Mnh!

21:34.598 --> 21:35.731
[DIALING, RINGING]

21:35.766 --> 21:37.366
- Sandra.
- SANDRA: Where's Allison?

21:37.401 --> 21:38.935
- At a hearing.
- Can you find her?

21:38.969 --> 21:41.070
Sandra, let me help you. What's going on?

21:41.104 --> 21:42.712
I need you to go to court,
get an injunction.

21:42.747 --> 21:44.240
The FBI is attempting
to unlawfully perform

21:44.274 --> 21:45.736
a CT scan on my client.

21:45.771 --> 21:47.873
GOODE: What are you doing? Hang
up the phone and move away.

21:47.908 --> 21:48.978
That's an order.

21:49.012 --> 21:50.947
Payano. The paperwork is on my desk.

21:50.981 --> 21:52.081
GOODE: Now!
- Now!

21:52.115 --> 21:53.082
I got you.

21:54.151 --> 21:56.085
This injunction will be granted
within the hour.

21:56.119 --> 21:57.086
I'm not moving until then.

21:57.120 --> 21:59.088
Sounds like we got an hour
to get this done.

21:59.122 --> 22:00.385
Move.

22:00.420 --> 22:03.359
I'm not scared of you,
and I'm not moving.

22:03.393 --> 22:05.428
♪

22:05.462 --> 22:07.029
Hey!

22:07.064 --> 22:08.064
Let go! [GRUNTS]

22:08.098 --> 22:09.432
Let go!

22:09.466 --> 22:10.867
You cannot do this!

22:10.901 --> 22:13.903
[HANDCUFFS CLICKING]

22:13.937 --> 22:16.239
You can't do this!

22:16.273 --> 22:17.907
It's done.

22:17.941 --> 22:19.008
Let's go.

22:31.049 --> 22:32.374
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

22:32.375 --> 22:34.109
MAN: All right, just slow,
steady breaths.

22:34.144 --> 22:35.511
[MONITORS BEEPING LOUDLY]

22:35.545 --> 22:36.579
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

22:36.613 --> 22:42.173
[HEART BEATING]

22:42.225 --> 22:43.292
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

22:43.386 --> 22:44.920
WOMAN: Nurses station.

22:44.954 --> 22:46.221
♪

22:46.255 --> 22:48.023
[GROANS]

22:48.057 --> 22:49.992
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

22:50.026 --> 22:55.163
♪

22:55.198 --> 23:00.168
♪

23:00.203 --> 23:07.676
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

23:07.710 --> 23:09.778
[MONITOR BEEPING LOUDLY]

23:09.812 --> 23:11.213
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

23:14.317 --> 23:15.717
Wait, wait.

23:16.417 --> 23:18.276
- What is going on?
- Sandra.

23:18.310 --> 23:20.022
- I'm going to need a full sentence.
- Sorry.

23:20.056 --> 23:21.223
Sandra's trapped at the hospital,

23:21.257 --> 23:22.858
and the FBI's trying to CT her client

23:22.892 --> 23:24.526
- without a warrant.
- What do you mean trapped?

23:24.560 --> 23:26.728
I don't think she's drowning in a moat
with crocodiles nipping at her feet,

23:26.763 --> 23:28.196
but she didn't sound good.

23:28.231 --> 23:30.098
I've got to go.

23:30.133 --> 23:31.733
[DOOR OPENS]

23:31.768 --> 23:37.406
♪

23:37.440 --> 23:40.075
- The aisle?
- Yes.

23:40.109 --> 23:41.743
Did someone die in one of these seats

23:41.778 --> 23:43.612
and you like to relive the memory or...?

23:43.646 --> 23:45.213
I just don't like to get
trapped in the middle.

23:45.248 --> 23:46.615
By what?

23:46.649 --> 23:47.916
ROGER: Sometimes it fills up.

23:47.950 --> 23:49.785
- With people?
- Sometimes.

23:49.819 --> 23:51.753
I saw "Sideways" here on opening night

23:51.788 --> 23:53.789
and must have been like 20% filled.

23:53.823 --> 23:55.157
Some people were drinking wine.

23:55.604 --> 23:56.971
It was pretty crazy.

23:57.706 --> 23:59.640
Move down.

24:02.632 --> 24:04.232
This is definitely "Wonder Woman," right?

24:04.267 --> 24:05.400
Uh-huh.

24:05.435 --> 24:08.503
Because the sign out front said
"Je T'aime, Coubert,"

24:08.538 --> 24:10.939
and I don't want to see some French movie

24:10.973 --> 24:12.307
set in a small village.

24:12.341 --> 24:14.142
Oh, that poster's been there for years.

24:14.177 --> 24:16.178
This is one of the few
independent theaters left

24:16.212 --> 24:17.345
in Westchester.

24:17.380 --> 24:18.680
A lot of random movies.

24:18.715 --> 24:20.315
But any movie, at this point.

24:20.349 --> 24:22.184
I can't remember the last time
I went to a movie.

24:22.736 --> 24:23.952
You never just go by yourself?

24:23.986 --> 24:26.574
I can do almost anything
by myself... prefer it...

24:26.608 --> 24:27.866
but that one?

24:28.691 --> 24:29.991
Always felt weird.

24:30.661 --> 24:33.662
Well, I'm glad we're here together, then.

24:37.233 --> 24:42.104
[CURTAIN MOTOR WHIRRING]

24:44.207 --> 24:45.874
<i>♪</i>

24:45.908 --> 24:47.776
WOMAN: <i>Je T'aime, Coubert.</i>

24:47.810 --> 24:50.779
[ <i>SPEAKING FRENCH</i> ]

24:50.813 --> 24:52.663
♪

24:52.697 --> 24:54.116
Just for the record, Natalie,

24:54.150 --> 24:56.551
what is your role within
Governor Shales' office?

24:56.586 --> 24:58.653
Short answer... I'm the
Deputy Political Director.

24:58.688 --> 24:59.821
Long answer?

24:59.856 --> 25:01.123
I do everything

25:01.157 --> 25:02.691
while Simon sits on an exercise ball

25:02.725 --> 25:03.903
and plays Solitaire.

25:03.937 --> 25:05.193
Natalie thinks she's my boss.

25:05.228 --> 25:06.394
She's not my boss.

25:06.429 --> 25:07.521
Did she tell you she's my boss?

25:07.556 --> 25:08.997
No. Let's talk about your actual boss.

25:09.031 --> 25:11.233
We have evidence that the
Governor's been seeking payment

25:11.267 --> 25:13.201
in exchange for a Senate appointment.

25:13.236 --> 25:15.036
Do you know anything about this, Daniel?

25:15.071 --> 25:16.705
I know Simon's asking Senate candidates

25:16.739 --> 25:17.739
for campaign commitments,

25:17.774 --> 25:19.407
but the Governor
doesn't know anything about it.

25:19.442 --> 25:20.709
Simon.

25:20.743 --> 25:21.977
He's trying to buy a promotion.

25:22.011 --> 25:23.208
It's not gonna work.

25:23.242 --> 25:26.042
Did the Governor ever ask you to
seek out money, goods, or services

25:26.077 --> 25:28.817
- from any potential Senate...
- Let me stop you there.

25:28.851 --> 25:31.153
Shales? Best boss ever.

25:31.187 --> 25:32.587
He's awesome.

25:32.622 --> 25:35.323
We have sources who say
he's a tough boss.

25:35.358 --> 25:36.224
Impossible to say no to.

25:36.259 --> 25:38.193
It's an honor to work for the Governor.

25:38.227 --> 25:39.361
He's one of the good ones. He's...

25:39.395 --> 25:40.362
He's the real deal.

25:40.396 --> 25:41.505
- Hardworking...
- honest...

25:41.539 --> 25:42.898
- He would never...
- in a million years...

25:42.932 --> 25:44.966
break the law,
and I'll say that in court.

25:45.868 --> 25:47.903
But, for real, did Natalie
say she's my supervisor?

25:47.937 --> 25:49.237
'Cause we're on the same level.

25:49.272 --> 25:50.205
I do not report to her.

25:50.239 --> 25:53.875
♪

25:53.910 --> 25:55.377
[SIGHS] Nothing.

25:55.411 --> 25:57.279
Not a single useful piece of information.

25:57.313 --> 25:59.773
- They're protecting Shales.
- They're protecting themselves.

25:59.807 --> 26:01.421
They don't want to go down with the ship.

26:01.455 --> 26:03.451
What about Tim Klein,
the Governor's chief of staff?

26:03.486 --> 26:05.220
Klein and Shales are tight, inseparable.

26:05.254 --> 26:06.254
- No way.
- I told you.

26:06.289 --> 26:07.389
We should've done a sting.

26:07.423 --> 26:08.790
It would've taken an hour.

26:08.825 --> 26:10.064
We'd control all the variables.

26:10.098 --> 26:12.460
Get Shales negotiating on the wire.

26:12.495 --> 26:13.862
If it only takes an hour,
we still got time.

26:13.896 --> 26:16.264
Mm, the FBI would need at least
half a day to prep an op.

26:16.299 --> 26:18.057
- An op?
- Anya taught her all the lingo.

26:18.092 --> 26:19.935
- She thinks she's an agent now.
- Anya?

26:19.969 --> 26:21.636
Actually, do you think Anya could help us

26:21.671 --> 26:23.438
- pull together a sting on the fly?
- Who's Anya?

26:23.472 --> 26:25.307
She's in the field tonight.

26:25.341 --> 26:27.375
Oh.

26:27.410 --> 26:28.810
♪

26:28.845 --> 26:31.379
- What?
- I'm not surprised you didn't tell me,

26:31.414 --> 26:33.114
- but I figured you'd know.
- Know what?

26:33.149 --> 26:35.435
You're... dating... Anya.

26:35.469 --> 26:36.747
- What?
- No.

26:36.782 --> 26:37.953
That's why you're not lonely

26:37.987 --> 26:39.195
and you don't need a pet

26:39.230 --> 26:40.322
and why you're late in the mornings,

26:40.356 --> 26:43.391
because you're <i>dating</i> Anya.

26:43.426 --> 26:46.696
An. Ya.

26:46.731 --> 26:47.796
[CHUCKLES]

26:47.830 --> 26:49.731
- You really didn't know?
- Nope.

26:49.765 --> 26:51.433
♪

26:51.467 --> 26:52.934
I thought you guys were tight.

26:52.969 --> 26:54.236
Well, there you have it.

26:54.270 --> 26:55.637
You think you know two people,

26:55.671 --> 26:57.939
and then they surprise you, and...

26:57.974 --> 26:59.698
- And that is it.
- What?

26:59.732 --> 27:01.476
- Tim Klein.
- I'm not dating Tim Klein.

27:01.510 --> 27:02.933
No. Listen.

27:02.968 --> 27:04.613
We've been assuming
that Klein and Governor Shales

27:04.647 --> 27:06.314
are joined at the hip
and that Klein is a dead end.

27:06.349 --> 27:09.451
But who knows how close
they really are, right?

27:09.485 --> 27:11.419
Shales is a narcissist
and a bully, like Leonard,

27:11.454 --> 27:12.692
and Klein is secretive

27:12.727 --> 27:14.522
and only conveniently
principled, like you.

27:14.557 --> 27:15.857
There's no way they're
as tight as they seem.

27:15.892 --> 27:17.525
Putting aside what you just said,

27:17.560 --> 27:18.583
what are you suggesting?

27:18.617 --> 27:19.828
Let's try to break Klein.

27:19.862 --> 27:20.762
We bring him in,

27:20.796 --> 27:22.430
bluff him on what
we have from the Governor

27:22.465 --> 27:23.999
that implicates him and see if he turns,

27:24.033 --> 27:25.300
just like you two
would turn on each other.

27:25.334 --> 27:28.270
- And if he calls our bluff?
- Then we lose,

27:28.304 --> 27:29.437
but we're gonna lose
if we don't do something.

27:29.472 --> 27:33.441
So let's bet on human vanity,
insecurity, and paranoia.

27:33.476 --> 27:34.476
This is great!

27:34.510 --> 27:40.282
♪

27:41.528 --> 27:48.814
♪

27:48.839 --> 27:50.569
SETH: Tim, thank you
for coming down here.

27:50.604 --> 27:51.762
What's this about?

27:51.797 --> 27:53.543
I think your client knows
what this is about.

27:53.578 --> 27:55.645
- I have no idea, actually.
- KATE: You know.

27:55.680 --> 27:58.415
The Governor is trying to sell
the open Senate seat.

27:58.449 --> 27:59.916
SETH: There's a room on the 22nd floor

27:59.951 --> 28:01.551
filled with incriminating evidence...

28:01.586 --> 28:04.254
recordings, e-mails, texts,

28:04.288 --> 28:06.356
personal exchanges
between you and the Governor

28:06.390 --> 28:07.722
using personal e-mail accounts.

28:07.756 --> 28:09.192
LEONARD: E-mails from
the Governor to his wife

28:09.227 --> 28:11.244
explicitly saying
that you were in on this

28:11.278 --> 28:12.251
from the beginning.

28:12.285 --> 28:13.358
KATE: You're looking at

28:13.392 --> 28:15.665
theft of honest services, conspiracy,

28:15.700 --> 28:17.500
and, depending on what you say in here,

28:17.535 --> 28:19.269
making false statements.

28:19.303 --> 28:22.005
All told, that's a 14-year sentence.

28:24.904 --> 28:27.468
This is the story
the Governor is telling,

28:27.502 --> 28:30.042
and as of now, we have no
reason not to believe him.

28:30.076 --> 28:32.349
But you have been a devoted civil servant

28:32.383 --> 28:33.883
your entire career.

28:33.918 --> 28:36.596
We felt the government
owed you one opportunity

28:36.631 --> 28:39.009
to come forward with your own story,

28:39.044 --> 28:41.725
one opportunity to help yourself.

28:41.759 --> 28:42.759
This is a stunt.

28:42.793 --> 28:44.861
You got nothing,
and you're gonna get nothing.

28:44.895 --> 28:46.830
Shut up for a second, will you?

28:48.418 --> 28:50.100
What about immunity?

28:50.670 --> 28:52.769
We want the Governor.

28:55.038 --> 28:57.627
The people always thought
Shales and I were close.

28:58.743 --> 29:01.711
Honestly, we weren't.

29:08.889 --> 29:10.323
JAY: I got it.

29:10.357 --> 29:12.125
The injunction.

29:12.159 --> 29:13.790
It's too late.

29:13.824 --> 29:14.894
Are you okay?

29:14.928 --> 29:16.496
What did they do to you?

29:16.530 --> 29:17.497
Are you okay?

29:18.115 --> 29:19.411
What's your name?

29:19.445 --> 29:20.867
You need to keep your distance, son.

29:20.901 --> 29:22.468
It's Staub.

29:22.503 --> 29:24.470
I need you to remove those
restraints, Officer Staub.

29:24.505 --> 29:25.605
That's not my call.

29:28.575 --> 29:29.976
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

29:30.010 --> 29:31.577
My name is Jay Simmons.

29:31.612 --> 29:33.146
I am a Federal Public Defender

29:33.180 --> 29:35.348
in the Southern District of New York.

29:36.091 --> 29:37.817
This is my colleague, Sandra Bell.

29:37.851 --> 29:40.253
She was handcuffed
to this railing by force

29:40.287 --> 29:42.755
and is being unlawfully detained
by the FBI.

29:42.790 --> 29:45.158
This is Officer Staub from the NYPD,

29:45.192 --> 29:47.093
who refuses to release Ms. Bell,

29:47.127 --> 29:49.562
despite repeated
reasonable requests to do so.

29:49.596 --> 29:52.665
I am holding in my hand
an order from a federal judge

29:52.699 --> 29:56.369
that the FBI and Officer Staub
are willfully ignoring

29:56.403 --> 29:58.571
by continuing to detain Ms. Bell.

29:58.605 --> 30:00.573
- [CELLPHONE BEEPS]
- This may not be your call,

30:00.607 --> 30:02.041
but with one push of a button,

30:02.076 --> 30:03.676
you will be the face of this mess.

30:03.710 --> 30:05.678
This video will be
on the phones and tablets

30:05.712 --> 30:06.679
of every New Yorker.

30:06.713 --> 30:08.014
All they're gonna see

30:08.048 --> 30:09.671
is this woman hunched over, shackled,

30:09.705 --> 30:11.784
and you standing there doing nothing.

30:11.819 --> 30:13.619
This may not be your call,

30:13.654 --> 30:16.189
but don't let it be your nightmare.

30:18.826 --> 30:22.962
♪

30:22.996 --> 30:25.364
[HANDCUFFS CLICK]

30:25.399 --> 30:26.732
Payano...

30:26.767 --> 30:28.568
the man they took away for the CT scan.

30:28.602 --> 30:31.070
Third floor. They're backed up.

30:31.105 --> 30:32.305
Hey.

30:32.339 --> 30:34.440
Can you run?

30:34.475 --> 30:37.096
I need you to get up and run.

30:37.130 --> 30:44.717
♪

30:44.751 --> 30:46.252
[BEEPS]

30:46.286 --> 30:50.156
♪

30:50.190 --> 30:51.757
- [DOOR OPENS]
- JAY: Stop!

30:52.493 --> 30:53.726
GOODE: [CHUCKLES]

30:53.760 --> 30:55.428
This is happening.

30:55.462 --> 30:56.629
This is a federal court order

30:56.663 --> 30:57.897
preventing you from going through

30:57.931 --> 30:59.699
with this illegal test.

31:01.001 --> 31:02.168
You can't do this.

31:02.202 --> 31:04.239
It's done.

31:04.273 --> 31:06.806
♪

31:06.840 --> 31:08.274
Cut it.

31:08.308 --> 31:10.910
[KEYS CLACKING]

31:10.944 --> 31:16.516
♪

31:16.550 --> 31:21.921
♪

31:21.955 --> 31:23.174
LEONARD: Call the Governor.

31:23.209 --> 31:26.159
Tell him the FBI just
showed up at your door.

31:26.193 --> 31:27.760
Ask what you should tell them.

31:29.963 --> 31:31.130
[PHONE BEEPS]

31:35.736 --> 31:37.803
[SIGHS]

31:41.408 --> 31:43.776
[RINGING]

31:43.810 --> 31:46.145
GOVERNOR SHALES: Hello? Tim?
You still at the office?

31:46.180 --> 31:47.647
No, I'm home.

31:47.681 --> 31:49.682
The FBI just showed up.

31:49.716 --> 31:51.551
They're asking about the Senate seat.

31:51.585 --> 31:54.187
The FBI is there now?

31:54.221 --> 31:55.788
They're looking around.
I'm in another room.

31:55.822 --> 31:57.823
I don't know what to tell them.

31:57.858 --> 31:59.625
Tell them the truth.
We have nothing to hide.

31:59.660 --> 32:01.661
We're not doing anything wrong.

32:01.695 --> 32:03.043
And if they want to talk to me,

32:03.078 --> 32:04.397
I'm happy to.

32:04.431 --> 32:06.966
Okay. I'll let you know how it goes.

32:07.000 --> 32:08.000
[PHONE BEEPS]

32:08.035 --> 32:10.770
[SIGHS]

32:14.775 --> 32:18.744
[CELLPHONE VIBRATING]

32:18.779 --> 32:20.076
What is that?

32:20.110 --> 32:21.847
It's [CLEARS THROAT] my burner phone.

32:21.882 --> 32:24.350
- Then what was this?
- My work phone.

32:24.384 --> 32:25.751
The Governor gave me another phone,

32:25.786 --> 32:27.386
just for him.

32:29.089 --> 32:30.022
Pick it up.

32:30.057 --> 32:31.123
Hello?

32:31.158 --> 32:32.792
GOVERNOR SHALES: You didn't
say anything, did you?

32:34.928 --> 32:36.028
No.

32:36.063 --> 32:39.198
Delete every text and e-mail

32:39.233 --> 32:40.366
about the Senate appointment.

32:40.400 --> 32:42.935
Destroy it, all of it, now.

32:42.970 --> 32:44.270
[PHONE CLICKS]

32:44.304 --> 32:48.708
♪

32:54.456 --> 32:56.024
JILL: Last stop.

32:56.058 --> 32:56.925
ROGER: It's a good one.

32:56.959 --> 32:58.726
Let me guess... Yankees are coming out.

32:58.760 --> 33:00.261
They are, tomorrow.

33:00.296 --> 33:01.296
Peekskill Yankees.

33:01.330 --> 33:04.198
Won the pennant 7 times
in the last 10 years.

33:04.233 --> 33:05.099
I have season tickets,

33:05.134 --> 33:06.701
if you want to draw up some contracts.

33:06.735 --> 33:08.202
I'm good.

33:09.605 --> 33:11.005
Maggie played on the team here

33:11.040 --> 33:12.891
when she was in 7th grade.

33:13.767 --> 33:15.834
First time she pitched,

33:15.869 --> 33:18.402
- she gave up 11 runs in 3 innings.
- Ouch!

33:18.437 --> 33:21.140
She was very disciplined.

33:21.174 --> 33:23.342
Second time out,
she had her ERA down to 6.

33:23.376 --> 33:26.211
She just kept chipping away at it.

33:26.246 --> 33:28.347
By the time Renee and the girls
moved away,

33:28.381 --> 33:30.916
she was one of the best
pitchers in Westchester.

33:30.951 --> 33:32.017
Sounds like her dad...

33:32.052 --> 33:35.421
not a lot of natural talent
but a really hard worker.

33:35.455 --> 33:37.556
[LAUGHING]

33:41.027 --> 33:42.928
I think I'd be better at it next time.

33:42.963 --> 33:44.330
- What?
- Marriage.

33:45.590 --> 33:46.732
Maybe.

33:46.766 --> 33:48.635
Takes practice.

33:49.269 --> 33:51.036
I'd be better at juggling chainsaws

33:51.071 --> 33:51.971
if I practiced.

33:52.005 --> 33:55.174
It's just not something
I'm interested in.

33:55.208 --> 33:57.242
You and Cliff... how was that?

33:57.277 --> 33:59.712
- What?
- The divorce.

34:01.448 --> 34:03.549
More fun than the marriage.

34:03.583 --> 34:05.050
You never talk about it.

34:05.085 --> 34:07.753
When would I talk about it,
in the bottom of the 7th?

34:07.787 --> 34:09.922
We're not always at a
baseball game, you and me.

34:09.956 --> 34:11.422
We are. That's who we are.

34:11.458 --> 34:13.225
We're people who go to the baseball game.

34:13.259 --> 34:15.194
Seems like we're people
who go to a movie, too.

34:15.228 --> 34:16.695
It was a metaphor.

34:16.730 --> 34:18.230
Kind of pretentious.

34:18.264 --> 34:20.899
Says the guy who took me to
"Je T'aime, Coubert"?

34:20.934 --> 34:22.467
That was a lovely little village.

34:22.502 --> 34:24.036
[LAUGHS]

34:30.443 --> 34:33.221
Cliff was a...

34:33.980 --> 34:35.723
mistake.

34:36.483 --> 34:39.051
Him, personally, yes,

34:39.085 --> 34:40.786
but it wasn't just him.

34:40.820 --> 34:43.789
I thought I wanted something else.

34:46.442 --> 34:48.027
I didn't.

34:49.929 --> 34:51.929
There's nothing more to it than that.

34:53.199 --> 34:55.100
There's a lot more to it than that.

34:55.135 --> 34:56.301
But it's a start.

34:56.335 --> 34:58.955
Thank you... for that.

34:59.673 --> 35:01.006
For today.

35:01.041 --> 35:03.475
It was a grand day out. It was.

35:07.280 --> 35:09.515
This could never work. You know that.

35:09.549 --> 35:10.482
I don't know that.

35:10.517 --> 35:13.352
We have fundamentally different
world views.

35:13.386 --> 35:16.021
We both believe fielding
percentage and batting average

35:16.056 --> 35:18.123
are totally overrated statistics.

35:18.158 --> 35:19.958
You know what I mean.

35:19.993 --> 35:22.795
Eventually... we'd be lying in bed,

35:22.829 --> 35:24.863
and I'd be infuriated...

35:24.898 --> 35:27.933
by something you said, something you did.

35:27.967 --> 35:30.669
I spent years lying next to someone

35:30.704 --> 35:32.705
I secretly hated...

35:32.739 --> 35:34.782
then openly hated.

35:35.809 --> 35:37.876
I'm never going back there.

35:38.661 --> 35:40.179
My takeaway from that is that

35:40.213 --> 35:42.347
- you've thought about us lying in bed.
- [SCOFFS]

35:46.086 --> 35:47.286
I wasn't proposing, Jill.

35:47.320 --> 35:49.621
I just... want you to know I like you.

35:54.194 --> 35:55.961
I like you, too.

35:55.995 --> 36:02.901
♪

36:02.936 --> 36:06.905
You'd think Jimmy Sant'Ambrogio
dying in front of me

36:06.940 --> 36:08.240
would mean something.

36:08.274 --> 36:09.675
It didn't, really.

36:09.709 --> 36:11.343
But...

36:15.615 --> 36:18.350
Maggie playing here...

36:20.120 --> 36:22.372
Last time I saw her pitch,

36:23.289 --> 36:25.424
I didn't know it was the last time.

36:25.458 --> 36:27.788
Thought it was just another warm night.

36:27.822 --> 36:29.895
♪

36:29.929 --> 36:32.548
Then they moved away, she quit playing.

36:34.342 --> 36:36.735
You think these moments
will last forever,

36:36.770 --> 36:38.403
and they do not.

36:38.438 --> 36:40.038
I understand that now.

36:40.073 --> 36:43.876
♪

36:43.910 --> 36:45.377
I do like you.

36:45.411 --> 36:53.252
♪

36:53.286 --> 36:58.791
[CELLPHONES RINGING]

36:58.825 --> 37:00.058
- Jill Carlan.
- Roger Gunn.

37:00.093 --> 37:01.727
♪

37:01.761 --> 37:03.428
Oh. Thank you.

37:03.463 --> 37:05.931
That sandwich came
out of a vending machine,

37:05.965 --> 37:06.899
so don't thank me

37:06.933 --> 37:08.700
until you eat it
and live through the night.

37:08.735 --> 37:11.236
- But we're in the right place.
- [CHUCKLES]

37:11.271 --> 37:14.106
Thank you for getting the injunction,

37:14.140 --> 37:16.041
getting me out of those restraints,

37:16.075 --> 37:17.385
getting me up.

37:18.111 --> 37:20.112
I needed that.

37:24.851 --> 37:27.986
My mom drove me to school every day.

37:28.021 --> 37:29.087
Every day she could.

37:29.122 --> 37:31.557
My dad would always tell her
to make me take the bus,

37:31.591 --> 37:34.159
but my mom thought it was our time,

37:34.194 --> 37:35.494
girls time.

37:35.528 --> 37:37.429
We would talk about everything...

37:37.463 --> 37:39.449
anything I wanted.

37:40.333 --> 37:42.734
But I took the bus that day.

37:42.769 --> 37:45.137
My mom had to go to work early.

37:45.171 --> 37:47.973
They were doing inventory that morning.

37:48.007 --> 37:52.244
My mom did the books
for this liquor store, Digg's.

37:52.278 --> 37:55.147
She used to bring me
little peppermints they sold.

37:55.181 --> 37:57.133
They were all over the house.

37:58.176 --> 37:59.985
And she put one in my hand that morning

38:00.019 --> 38:04.623
and said, "Girl talk, back on tomorrow."

38:09.362 --> 38:10.996
I knew something awful happened

38:11.030 --> 38:12.865
when Ms. Sutton pulled me out of my class

38:12.899 --> 38:14.867
and told me to go
to the principal's office.

38:14.901 --> 38:17.002
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

38:17.036 --> 38:19.238
My dad was waiting there.

38:21.641 --> 38:23.342
He was crying.

38:24.994 --> 38:27.446
He told me what I already knew.

38:29.148 --> 38:31.083
My mom was hurt.

38:32.794 --> 38:34.553
She was in a car accident.

38:34.587 --> 38:36.788
♪

38:36.823 --> 38:39.224
I wanted to see her.

38:39.259 --> 38:41.994
But my dad kept saying she'd be okay.

38:42.028 --> 38:44.162
That's what the doctors told him.

38:44.722 --> 38:46.865
They told me to sit and wait,

38:46.900 --> 38:49.668
just... wait.

38:49.702 --> 38:52.871
♪

38:52.906 --> 38:56.208
But I wanted to get up

38:56.242 --> 38:58.911
and go in that room and see her.

38:58.945 --> 39:02.953
♪

39:02.988 --> 39:05.217
I should have.

39:05.251 --> 39:07.319
♪

39:07.353 --> 39:08.587
But I didn't.

39:08.621 --> 39:10.623
I sat there.

39:12.058 --> 39:13.659
Until someone came to me.

39:13.693 --> 39:23.602
♪

39:23.636 --> 39:33.612
♪

39:33.646 --> 39:35.514
I swore I would never sit down again

39:35.548 --> 39:37.516
when I didn't want to.

39:37.550 --> 39:41.787
I vowed to always ask questions.

39:41.821 --> 39:43.889
♪

39:43.923 --> 39:45.590
I never wanted to feel like

39:45.625 --> 39:48.327
I wasn't in control ever again.

39:49.228 --> 39:51.396
I owe that to my mom.

39:51.431 --> 40:00.305
♪

40:00.340 --> 40:02.407
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

40:03.643 --> 40:04.643
[SIGHS]

40:04.677 --> 40:09.081
♪

40:09.115 --> 40:11.116
- Are you okay?
- I... I'm fine.

40:11.150 --> 40:12.985
You look... okay.

40:13.019 --> 40:14.319
I'm okay.

40:14.354 --> 40:15.620
I called Jill because I was worried.

40:15.655 --> 40:17.255
Jay had my back.

40:17.290 --> 40:18.223
All good.

40:18.257 --> 40:19.853
♪

40:19.888 --> 40:21.827
Well, my motion to dismiss was granted,

40:21.861 --> 40:23.628
and I'm feeling generous...

40:23.663 --> 40:25.497
and guilty for not being there for you.

40:25.531 --> 40:28.133
So, drinks? On me?

40:28.167 --> 40:29.334
All of us?

40:29.983 --> 40:31.336
JILL: Yes.

40:31.371 --> 40:33.772
<i>This just in... we have breaking news.</i>

40:33.806 --> 40:36.508
<i>Governor Shales was arrested
mere minutes ago</i>

40:36.542 --> 40:38.243
<i>for obstruction of justice.</i>

40:38.277 --> 40:40.612
<i>The FBI now has him in custody.</i>

40:40.646 --> 40:42.147
Nicely done.

40:43.466 --> 40:45.450
- It was a team effort.
- I'm sure it was.

40:45.485 --> 40:47.319
Of course, I told Delap it was largely me

40:47.353 --> 40:49.628
because I'm your boss
and that's what bosses do.

40:50.723 --> 40:52.257
But he's... he's very happy

40:52.291 --> 40:53.458
with the three of you right now.

40:53.493 --> 40:55.627
Come on. I'll buy you guys a drink.

40:55.661 --> 40:58.830
♪ Stop fearing you won't be the one ♪

40:59.866 --> 41:01.150
Hey.

41:02.068 --> 41:03.168
Maybe I should've said something.

41:03.202 --> 41:04.236
You didn't owe me that.

41:04.270 --> 41:06.304
I don't tell you every time
I go out with someone.

41:06.339 --> 41:08.273
- Uh, yeah, you do.
- Oh. Right.

41:08.307 --> 41:11.410
Well, look, I'm happy for you.

41:11.911 --> 41:13.111
You like this girl?

41:13.146 --> 41:14.312
Yeah, I kind of do.

41:14.347 --> 41:15.391
Then good.

41:16.025 --> 41:18.850
I told you, you're a catch.

41:18.885 --> 41:19.851
♪

41:19.886 --> 41:21.286
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

41:21.320 --> 41:24.389
♪ We won't make it keeping to our own ♪

41:24.424 --> 41:27.225
♪

41:27.260 --> 41:31.229
♪ No, it's not easy ♪

41:31.264 --> 41:34.666
♪ Through the long shadow,
you can't see the road ♪

41:34.700 --> 41:37.636
♪

41:37.670 --> 41:41.640
♪ I know it's not easy ♪

41:41.674 --> 41:45.043
